{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"a1a08151ad67a0c5d","tool_use_id":"toolu_01GGSMyoXVHYzdjtsDxebzpc","description":"Review against improvement plan","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Compare the actual code changes in lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts (iteration 30, current HEAD) against the improvement plan at tools/title-loop/docs/30-a2f9b6c/improvement-plan.md.\n\nThe improvement plan specifies 4 changes:\n1. Preserve standalone candidate when continuation-merging (fix 6/9 failures)\n2. Add \"sole\" to food dictionary (fix 1 failure)  \n3. Lower word-count threshold for Polish cooking instruction detection (fix 1 failure)\n4. Raise positional cap to 0.22 for pipe+ALL_CAPS (fix 1 failure)\n\nRead both files and check:\n\nA. **Plan adherence**: Were all 4 planned changes implemented correctly? Any deviations from the plan?\n\nB. **Unplanned changes**: The diff includes several changes NOT in the improvement plan:\n   - `stripTrailingPageRef` function (new)\n   - OCR normalization in `passesHardFilters` (4→a before cooking instruction check)\n   - Multi-word garbled camelCase detection in `isLikelyGarbled`\n   - `hasErraticCasing` threshold change (3→5)\n   - Expanded `applyBlindOcrRepairToken` (4→A, 5→S, ¡→I, €→E, Í/Ì→I)\n   - Metadata check in 2-line/3-line joins\n   - Mc/Mac exemption in garbled detection\n   - New prefix filter for pre-merged continuation singles\n   \n   For each unplanned change: is it clearly beneficial, or does it risk regressions? Does it have test coverage?\n\nC. **Plan correctness**: The plan predicted 8 of 9 failures would be fixed. Does the implementation match this prediction?\n\nRead the files and provide a detailed comparison. Do NOT make code changes.","uuid":"53ed787c-62dc-4e89-a2c1-de2a1de2113a","session_id":"cda1f0b1-248e-469a-8a6a-1e44556e08de"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Compare the actual code changes in lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts (iteration 30, current HEAD) against the improvement plan at tools/title-loop/docs/30-a2f9b6c/improvement-plan.md.\n\nThe improvement plan specifies 4 changes:\n1. Preserve standalone candidate when continuation-merging (fix 6/9 failures)\n2. Add \"sole\" to food dictionary (fix 1 failure)  \n3. Lower word-count threshold for Polish cooking instruction detection (fix 1 failure)\n4. Raise positional cap to 0.22 for pipe+ALL_CAPS (fix 1 failure)\n\nRead both files and check:\n\nA. **Plan adherence**: Were all 4 planned changes implemented correctly? Any deviations from the plan?\n\nB. **Unplanned changes**: The diff includes several changes NOT in the improvement plan:\n   - `stripTrailingPageRef` function (new)\n   - OCR normalization in `passesHardFilters` (4→a before cooking instruction check)\n   - Multi-word garbled camelCase detection in `isLikelyGarbled`\n   - `hasErraticCasing` threshold change (3→5)\n   - Expanded `applyBlindOcrRepairToken` (4→A, 5→S, ¡→I, €→E, Í/Ì→I)\n   - Metadata check in 2-line/3-line joins\n   - Mc/Mac exemption in garbled detection\n   - New prefix filter for pre-merged continuation singles\n   \n   For each unplanned change: is it clearly beneficial, or does it risk regressions? Does it have test coverage?\n\nC. **Plan correctness**: The plan predicted 8 of 9 failures would be fixed. Does the implementation match this prediction?\n\nRead the files and provide a detailed comparison. Do NOT make code changes."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01GGSMyoXVHYzdjtsDxebzpc","session_id":"cda1f0b1-248e-469a-8a6a-1e44556e08de","uuid":"34b1a016-597c-4502-8f6d-09970dd15288"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FDW2pG466u24cVwtGN756A","type":"tool_result","content":"   290→    \"was\", \"one\", \"our\", \"out\", \"are\", \"has\", \"his\", \"how\", \"its\", \"may\",\n   291→    \"new\", \"now\", \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"who\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\",\n   292→    \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n   293→  ]);\n   294→  // Count all Unicode letters (not just ASCII) so Polish words like \"Żur\" (3 letters) pass\n   295→  const unicodeLetters = text.trim().replace(/[^a-zA-ZąćęłńóśźżĄĆĘŁŃÓŚŹŻ]/g, \"\");\n   296→  if (words.length === 1 && unicodeLetters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n   297→    return true;\n   298→  }\n   299→\n   300→  // Single word with internal lowercase→uppercase transition — OCR noise (e.g., \"UuIw\", \"aBC\")\n   301→  // No recipe title uses this pattern as a standalone single-word candidate.\n   302→  if (words.length === 1 && /[a-z][A-Z]/.test(text.trim()) && !/^(Mc|Mac)[A-Z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n   303→    return true;\n   304→  }\n   305→\n   306→  // Recipe titles never start with a lowercase letter\n   307→  if (/^[a-z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n   308→    return true;\n   309→  }\n   310→\n   311→  // Mid-text sentence boundary (\". \" followed by a letter) — body text fragment spliced from multiple sentences\n   312→  const trimmed = text.trim();\n   313→  if (/\\.\\s+[a-zA-Z]/.test(trimmed) && !trimmed.endsWith(\")\")) {\n   314→    return true;\n   315→  }\n   316→\n   317→  // Multi-word candidate containing a garbled OCR fragment: a short lowercase word that isn't a known short word\n   318→  if (words.length >= 2) {\n   319→    const commonShort2 = new Set([\n   320→      \"a\", \"i\", \"of\", \"or\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"is\", \"it\", \"an\",\n   321→      \"as\", \"at\", \"by\", \"do\", \"go\", \"if\", \"no\", \"so\", \"up\", \"we\",\n   322→      \"w\", \"z\",   // Polish prepositions (basic)\n   323→      \"ze\", \"bo\", \"na\", \"ni\", \"po\", \"ku\", \"od\", \"za\", \"co\",  // Polish prepositions (extended)\n   324→    ]);\n   325→    const hasGarbledWord = words.some(\n   326→      (w) =>\n   327→        /^[a-z]/.test(w) &&\n   328→        w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\").length <= 2 &&\n   329→        !commonShort2.has(w.toLowerCase())\n   330→    );\n   331→    if (hasGarbledWord) {\n   332→      return true;\n   333→    }\n   334→\n   335→    // Multi-word candidate with a garbled token: a short word with internal\n   336→    // lowercase→uppercase transition. Length capped at 7 to avoid false positives\n   337→    // from OCR-dropped-space artifacts (\"withGarlic\" = 10 chars). True garbled\n   338→    // tokens like \"XxYyZz\" or \"UuIw\" are ≤7 chars.\n   339→    // Narrow exemption: Mc/Mac name prefixes only (e.g., \"McDonald\").\n   340→    const hasGarbledCamelCase = words.some(\n   341→      (w) =>\n   342→        w.length >= 3 &&\n   343→        w.length <= 7 &&\n   344→        /[a-z][A-Z]/.test(w) &&\n   345→        !/^(Mc|Mac)[A-Z]/.test(w)\n   346→    );\n   347→    if (hasGarbledCamelCase) {\n   348→      return true;\n   349→    }\n   350→  }\n   351→\n   352→  return false;\n   353→}\n   354→\n   355→const COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS = /^(beat|fold|stir|mix|add|pour|bake|cook|cool|remove|place|combine|whisk|knead|roll|spread|brush|slice|chop|dice|mince|drain|rinse|peel|grate|melt|simmer|boil|fry|sauté|saute|roast|grill|broil|steam|let|set|transfer|serve|garnish|arrange|sprinkle|season|preheat|cover|uncover|reduce|bring|toss|cut|trim|shape|form|scatter|score|pat|rub|skim|strain|heat|discard|rest|marinate|wrap|flip|turn|layer|stuff|drizzle|squeeze|zest|soak|thaw|freeze|chill|warm|toast|crush|pound|crack|break|separate|weigh|measure|sift|dust|coat|dip|dredge|baste|debone|butterfly|truss|shred|puree|blend|process|pulse|whip|cream|proof|rise|punch|divide|portion|assemble)\\b/i;\n   356→\n   357→// Polish imperative cooking verbs (with OCR-resilient forms — no diacritics required).\n   358→// These cover the most common recipe instruction starters. Includes common OCR-corrupted\n   359→// forms (e.g., \"Smaż\" → \"Smaz\", \"Dodaj\" → \"Dodaj\").\n   360→// Note: only verbs that NEVER start a recipe title. \"Piecz\" (bake) is excluded because\n   361→// \"Pieczeń\" (roast) and \"Pieczarki\" (mushrooms) share the prefix.\n   362→// Use a Unicode-aware word-boundary lookahead instead of \\b, because JS \\b does not recognise\n   363→// Polish letters (ą ć ę ł ń ó ś ź ż) as word characters. Without this, `smaż\\b` would\n   364→// incorrectly match \"Smażona\" since \\b fires between ż (non-\\w) and the following o (\\w).\n   365→const POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS = /^(podawaj|dodaj|dodawaj|sma[zż]|gotuj|odced[zź]|wymieszaj|mieszaj|wlej|nalej|przygotuj|zagotuj|pokr[oó]j|obierz|wrzuc|wrzuć|usma[zż]|podsma[zż]|prze[lł][oó][zż]|zblenduj|ubij|roztrzepaj|rozprowad[zź]|wyrob|zamieszaj|posyp|polej|odstaw|na[lł][oó][zż]|przykryj|odkryj|wstaw|zdejmij|ods[aą]cz|rozgrzej|posiekaj|zetrzyj|wy[lł][oó][zż]|wyjmij|ukr[oó]j|przekr[oó]j|formuj|ugniataj|rozwałkuj|ugotuj|ugotowa[cć]|upiecz|podawa[cć]|zapiekaj|obtocz|obtoczy[cć]|podgrzej|podgrzewaj)(?![a-zA-ZąćęłńóśźżĄĆĘŁŃÓŚŹŻ])/i;\n   366→\n   367→function looksLikeCookingInstruction(text: string): boolean {\n   368→  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n   369→  // Polish cooking instructions are commonly 2-3 words (\"Ugotuj ziemniaki.\", \"Upiecz chleb.\")"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XjLSauSC3oNEccjMzcEMnr","session_id":"cda1f0b1-248e-469a-8a6a-1e44556e08de","uuid":"0c507c76-9e64-4c6a-9e0e-e93475a50927"}
