n that were implemented in the iteration 30 codebase (the baseline) rather than being newly added in this commit. The genuinely new unplanned additions in this commit are:\n\n- The `hasErraticCasing` length threshold change (3→5) — low risk, minor reduction in false garbled detections for 3–4 char words\n- The metadata guard in 2-line/3-line joins — low-medium risk, beneficial but lacks targeted test coverage\n- The pre-merged continuation prefix single filter (lines 1512–1528) — necessary companion to Change 1, correctly scoped, no dedicated test\n\nThe pre-merged continuation prefix single filter (item 8) is the most important unplanned addition. It is a required correctness fix for Change 1: without it, the `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS` and `Baked Eggs` regression cases the plan's watchlist warned about would materialize. Its inclusion demonstrates that the implementer worked through the downstream consequences of Change 1 fully. It should have been listed in the plan.\n\n**C. Plan correctness:** The prediction that Changes 1–3 fix 7 of 8 targeted failures is well-grounded. Change 4's effectiveness depends on a specific MiniLM score threshold that was not measured before implementation — this is the one prediction that carries non-trivial uncertainty. The unfixable Mushroom Risotto case is correctly identified and excluded."}],"totalDurationMs":133006,"totalTokens":48900,"totalToolUseCount":14,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6692,"cache_read_input_tokens":37931,"output_tokens":4276,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6692},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
