{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GbXw63pVtbUVb8567cybkK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\n     2→& Coriander\n     3→Baked eggs is one of my all-time favourite breakfast dishes. There is no joy greater than that of plunging in a piece of bread and pulling it out coated in unctuous egg yolk and whatever else goes with the eggs. Ilike my eggs spicy. Chilli provides a great way ofkick-starting your metabolism in the morning and harissa is a versatile condiment to have in the house for quick dishes. Chunks of wonderfully salty, creamy feta provide the perfect match for harissa. This versatile breakfast dish has been relied on for many wonderful evening meals in my home.\n     4→SERVES *\n     5→4 tbsp olive oil\n     6→5 garlic cloves, bashed and thinly sliced\n     7→3 large red onions, cut in half and sliced into 1em- (½in-) thick half moons\n     8→2 tsp turmeric\n     9→1 tsp ground coriander\n    10→I tsp ground cumin\n    11→½ tsp ground cinnamon\n    12→3 tbsp harissa\n    13→6 large tomatoes, roughly chopped\n    14→400g can chopped tomatoes\n    15→sea salt flakes\n    16→2 x 20g packets of coriander, leaves picked and roughly chopped 400g (14oz) feta cheese freshly ground black pepper 8 large free-range eggs\n    17→* To make the sauce, preheat a saucepan over a medium heat and drizzle in just enough oil to lightly coat the base of the pan. Sauté the garlie slivers and onion slices until they begin to soften and become translucent. Add the turmeric, ground coriander, cumin and cinnamon and stir well before adding the harissa paste. Put in the fresh and canned tomatoes, season generously with sea salt flakes and give everything a good stir, then reduce the temperature slightly and allow the sauce to cook for 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.\n    18→* Preheat the oven to 180°C/fan 160°C/gas mark 4. Select a large baking dish (or 2 smaller dishes) and pour the spicy tomato sauce into it. Scatter the chopped coriander on to the sauce (but save a handful for garnishing the finished dish) and give the mixture a very gentle stir to loosely incorporate the chopped leaves into the sauce. Break off 2.5cm (lin) rustic chunks of the feta and dot them all around the dish, pushing some down under the sauce and leaving some on the surface. Make 8 evenly spaced craters in the surface and crack your eggs into them, season the dish well with black pepper and another sprinkling of sea salt flakes, then bake for 10-12 minutes, or until the whites of the eggs have turned opaque and are cooked through.\n    19→* Remove from the oven, sprinkle the last handful of chopped coriander leaves over the dish and serve with ortancend (see page 55) is ideal as you can"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cda1f0b1-248e-469a-8a6a-1e44556e08de","uuid":"f511a381-6881-4623-98ea-6783a14bef91","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander.real.txt","content":"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\n& Coriander\nBaked eggs is one of my all-time favourite breakfast dishes. There is no joy greater than that of plunging in a piece of bread and pulling it out coated in unctuous egg yolk and whatever else goes with the eggs. Ilike my eggs spicy. Chilli provides a great way ofkick-starting your metabolism in the morning and harissa is a versatile condiment to have in the house for quick dishes. Chunks of wonderfully salty, creamy feta provide the perfect match for harissa. This versatile breakfast dish has been relied on for many wonderful evening meals in my home.\nSERVES *\n4 tbsp olive oil\n5 garlic cloves, bashed and thinly sliced\n3 large red onions, cut in half and sliced into 1em- (½in-) thick half moons\n2 tsp turmeric\n1 tsp ground coriander\nI tsp ground cumin\n½ tsp ground cinnamon\n3 tbsp harissa\n6 large tomatoes, roughly chopped\n400g can chopped tomatoes\nsea salt flakes\n2 x 20g packets of coriander, leaves picked and roughly chopped 400g (14oz) feta cheese freshly ground black pepper 8 large free-range eggs\n* To make the sauce, preheat a saucepan over a medium heat and drizzle in just enough oil to lightly coat the base of the pan. Sauté the garlie slivers and onion slices until they begin to soften and become translucent. Add the turmeric, ground coriander, cumin and cinnamon and stir well before adding the harissa paste. Put in the fresh and canned tomatoes, season generously with sea salt flakes and give everything a good stir, then reduce the temperature slightly and allow the sauce to cook for 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.\n* Preheat the oven to 180°C/fan 160°C/gas mark 4. Select a large baking dish (or 2 smaller dishes) and pour the spicy tomato sauce into it. Scatter the chopped coriander on to the sauce (but save a handful for garnishing the finished dish) and give the mixture a very gentle stir to loosely incorporate the chopped leaves into the sauce. Break off 2.5cm (lin) rustic chunks of the feta and dot them all around the dish, pushing some down under the sauce and leaving some on the surface. Make 8 evenly spaced craters in the surface and crack your eggs into them, season the dish well with black pepper and another sprinkling of sea salt flakes, then bake for 10-12 minutes, or until the whites of the eggs have turned opaque and are cooked through.\n* Remove from the oven, sprinkle the last handful of chopped coriander leaves over the dish and serve with ortancend (see page 55) is ideal as you can","numLines":19,"startLine":1,"totalLines":19}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XyumzemW7LU8sjb2nmEacV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Smażona zielona fasolka\n     2→GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\n     3→그린빈 볶음\n     4→Wymyslitem ten pireepis, gøy zomleszkotam we francji Laczy or amul kaneolckle i fanciste\n     5→Maj migz, ktöry Jest Froncuzem, przepode zo to fenelike.\n     6→DLA & OSOB\n     7→Przvgetowanie\n     8→15 minut\n     9→Smazenie 15 minut\n    10→SKLADNIKI\n    11→500 g cienkiej zielonej\n    12→fasolk\n    13→100 g wędzonego\n    14→boczku\n    15→10 zabków czosnku\n    16→2 lyzki mat ganjang (s.146)\n    17→2 łyzki nasion sezamu\n    18→3 łyzki oliwy z oliwek\n    19→1 łyzeczko soll\n    20→Odetnij ogorki fosolkı W gorsku zogotuş ossteng wode sita de mes fosolke Gotul ja pizer 2 minuty (mierzone od mementu peronets zagotowanit) Po tym czesie odcedt fasolke i or zelej je strumerite zimnej wody Obierz czosnek i przekrd zabki no pöt by usunge wietk Boczek pokrój no kowotki o grubośei 1 um Dektodhie rozgiel\n    21→nasiono sezamu\n    22→No potelni rozprowadż oliwę z oliwek i smaż crosnek na duzym ogr\n    23→82 się lekko zrumieni. Dodaj bøczek i usmaz Kiedy boczek jest jut ge towy, dodaj fasolke i mat gorjong Smaż przet 5 minut. Dodej rotgne cione nasiona sezamu i doprow solą Smaż jeszeze przez 2 minuty\n    24→Podawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\n    25→64"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cda1f0b1-248e-469a-8a6a-1e44556e08de","uuid":"d1fceaf9-7e44-43ad-a68e-0a6e1037b83b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Smażona zielona fasolka.real.txt","content":"Smażona zielona fasolka\nGREEN BEANS BORKEUM\n그린빈 볶음\nWymyslitem ten pireepis, gøy zomleszkotam we francji Laczy or amul kaneolckle i fanciste\nMaj migz, ktöry Jest Froncuzem, przepode zo to fenelike.\nDLA & OSOB\nPrzvgetowanie\n15 minut\nSmazenie 15 minut\nSKLADNIKI\n500 g cienkiej zielonej\nfasolk\n100 g wędzonego\nboczku\n10 zabków czosnku\n2 lyzki mat ganjang (s.146)\n2 łyzki nasion sezamu\n3 łyzki oliwy z oliwek\n1 łyzeczko soll\nOdetnij ogorki fosolkı W gorsku zogotuş ossteng wode sita de mes fosolke Gotul ja pizer 2 minuty (mierzone od mementu peronets zagotowanit) Po tym czesie odcedt fasolke i or zelej je strumerite zimnej wody Obierz czosnek i przekrd zabki no pöt by usunge wietk Boczek pokrój no kowotki o grubośei 1 um Dektodhie rozgiel\nnasiono sezamu\nNo potelni rozprowadż oliwę z oliwek i smaż crosnek na duzym ogr\n82 się lekko zrumieni. Dodaj bøczek i usmaz Kiedy boczek jest jut ge towy, dodaj fasolke i mat gorjong Smaż przet 5 minut. Dodej rotgne cione nasiona sezamu i doprow solą Smaż jeszeze przez 2 minuty\nPodawaj no gorqco lub na zimno\n64","numLines":25,"startLine":1,"totalLines":25}}}
